Description: Modular Linux distribution based on Ubuntu/Debian
 Nexus Linux is a modern, modular operating system built on top of Ubuntu LTS
 and Debian, featuring:
 .
  * Independent, modular applications for settings, desktop management, and
    system administration
  * Support for multiple desktop environments (Hyprland, KDE, XFCE, etc.)
  * Graphical installer with profile-based setup
  * First-class gaming support with Steam, Proton, and Wine
  * Automatic driver and firmware management
  * System snapshots and rollback functionality
  * Update management with kernel selection
  * Modern Qt6-based user interface
 .
 This package provides the core Nexus Linux infrastructure.
